    "body": "### Problem\n\nOne for @fwalch \r\n\r\nAFAIK LuaJIT works on ARM (as of [2.1](https://luajit.org/status.html)) - there are `arm64` packages of LuaJIT 2.1 ( Lua 5.1) or both current LTS releases (focal 20.04 and jammy 22.04).\r\n\r\nThe PPA (nightly) build script turns off LuaJIT for ARM.\r\n\r\n```\r\n# Force Lua on architectures where Luajit doesn't work\r\nifneq (,$(filter arm64,$(shell dpkg-architecture -qDEB_HOST_ARCH 2>/dev/null)))\r\n  CMAKE_EXTRA_FLAGS += -DPREFER_LUA=ON\r\nelse\r\n  CMAKE_EXTRA_FLAGS += -DPREFER_LUA=OFF\r\nendif\r\n```\r\n\r\nJust manually built on my Pi4 (ARM 8) and it reports LuaJIT support, and LazyVim (which checks and demands LuaJIT) works fine.\r\n\r\nAny chance of updating the PPA build scripts so they support ARM on LuaJIT 2.1?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Install nvim nightly on your Pi4 running Ubuntu 22.04\r\n- `nvim -V1 -v | grep 'LuaJIT.*'` returns nothing\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```\r\n$ nvim -V1 -v | grep LuaJIT.*\r\nLuaJIT 2.1.1705947465\r\n```\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nnightly PPA\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 22.04 (arm64)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty (but running byobu remotely via ssh)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nUbuntu PPA (unstable)",
